arts.ttl: Fenerbahce and Rangers win their openers in the revamped Europa League
arts.sum: Fenerbahce opened the revamped Europa League with a 2-1 home win over Belgian club Union Saint-Gilloise with both teams finishing the game with 10 men on Thursday. Defender Çağlar Söyüncü opened the scoring for Jose Mourinho’s team in the 26th with a half-volley from close range and Christian Burgess’ own goal in the 82nd made it 2-0 for Fenerbahce.

arts.ttl: Turkey basketball coach sparks outrage with Fenerbahce-Galatasaray gesture
arts.sum: Ergin Atman taunted Fernerbahce supporters after their Super Lig derby defeat to their fierce rivals

arts.ttl: Jose Mourinho SLAMS 'disrespectful' rivals Galatasaray while explaining why he didn't attend his post-match Fenerbahce press conference after heavy defeat
arts.sum: Jose Mourinho has fumed at Turkish rivals Galatasaray for being 'disrespectful' after he refused to attend his post-match press conference following Fenerbahce's shock Super Lig defeat.
